  "conclusion": "The c4 full-native/no-rowchunk context blocker is a native batched context producer issue, not KV cache addressing or output-buffer aliasing. Native batch context is red at row3 ([137,137,137,118]); routing native batch context through a temporary output buffer or compact copied cache preserves the same red row3 signature. Both per-row context+gate replay and per-row context-only replay are green ([137]*4), proving that the gate and post-context suffix can consume correct per-row context. The next retained-fix target is therefore the native grouped full-attention context producer / pre-QKV setup for the four-row no-rowchunk group. No throughput claim is made. During the required active c2 verify for this iteration, the first run reproduced the intermittent [103,137] c2 failure under serial_lm_head/selected_c1_batch/full-native metadata; an immediate repeat returned [137,137]. Treat c2 equality stability as an open blocker even though the current repeat is green.",
